Sales Performance Dashboard (Excel)
ðŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project analyzes sales transaction data to uncover trends, performance drivers, and customer purchasing behavior. The dashboard was built in Microsoft Excel using PivotTables, PivotCharts, slicers, and calculated fields to support business decision-making.

ðŸŽ¯ Objectives

Measure overall sales performance

Identify top-performing products and cities

Analyze sales trends over time (monthly, weekly, hourly)

Understand customer purchasing patterns

Provide actionable business insights

ðŸ§¾ Dataset Description

The dataset contains order-level sales data with the following fields:

Order ID

Product

Quantity Ordered

Price Each

Sales

Order Date

City

Month

Hour

Day of Week

Estimated Profit (calculated)

ðŸ”‘ Key KPIs

Total Sales

Total Orders

Units Sold (Total Quantity Ordered)

Estimated Profit

Top-Selling Product

Top-Selling City

ðŸ“ˆ Dashboard Features

Monthly Sales Trend to identify seasonality

Weekly Sales Analysis to compare day-of-week performance

Hourly Sales Trend to detect peak purchasing periods

Top Products Analysis to understand revenue drivers

Geographic Analysis highlighting top-performing cities

Interactive Slicers (Month, Day of Week, Hour) for dynamic filtering

ðŸ’¡ Key Insights

San Francisco is the top-selling city, driven mainly by high-value electronics.

MacBook Pro laptops generate the highest revenue among all products.

Sales show strong seasonal patterns, with higher performance in peak months.

Evening hours record the highest sales activity, indicating after-work purchasing behavior.

Certain weekdays consistently outperform others, suggesting opportunities for targeted promotions.

